profile_positions.description:
Research roles
- Perform research on reproductive/maternal health, sexually-transmitted/genital infections and reproductive tract microbiota with a Global Health perspective;
- Supervise research in: sexual, reproductive and maternal health, with a focus on Global Health.

Education Development and Management roles
- PhD coordinator, GROW Research School for Oncology and Developmental Biology;
- Management Team member, GROW Research School for Oncology and Developmental Biology;
- Coordinator of courses, BSc in Public Health and Biomedical Sciences and MSc in Medicine and Global Health;
- Team leader, development and redesign of courses for BSc or MSc students in Medicine, Global Health, Biomedical Sciences and Public Health;
- Member of the Educational Program Committee for Biomedical Sciences;
- Member of the Portfolio Assessment Committee for Biomedical Sciences;
- Member of the faculty-wide Taskforce on Students’ Employability;
- Education coordinator for Institute for Public Health Genomics;
- Biomedical Sciences programme representative within the faculty committee for the implementation of governmental policy changes in higher education.

Supervision of PhD students
-graduation Dec 2014, thesis focus on Sexually-Transmitted Infections (STIs) in NL
-graduation Dec 2018, thesis focus on STIs in India
-graduation Jan 2021, thesis focus on STIs and pregnancy in sub-Saharan Africa
-ongoing on microorganisms in expectant mothers

Teaching roles
- Lecturer and tutor for BSc and MSc students of Medicine, Global Health, Health Sciences, European Public Health and Biomedical Sciences Programs;
- Supervisor MSc/BSc Theses in Global Health, Public Health, Medicine, Biomedical Sciences (>50 completed);
- Supervisor of scientific research internships for Medical students;
- Scientific writing, cultural diversity and clinical communication trainer;
- Mentor for Medicine, Biomedical Sciences, Global Studies and Public Health (BSc and MSc) 60/70+ students/year.

-International consultant in academic sector development:
Coordinated the development of 4 innovative challenge-based university bachelor and master programs across 3 campuses of a private technical university in Mexico;
Developed workshops and implemented training tools in scientific communication and dissemination across 4 different academic institutions in 2 Southern African countries.

Supervise and support virtual mentor/mentees work;
Advise program administrator;
Facilitate and improve implementation of the program;
Provide engagement tactics.

Mentoring young women around the world wanting to start, or in the early stages of, a STEM career;
Empowering young women globally in the scientific fields;
Supporting the development of diversity workforce in the STEM field around the world;
Contribution to the project blog https://1000girls1000futures.blog/
